{"id": "EUVD-2024-53358", "enisaUuid": "1af1aef6-d803-3c31-99a2-c6dcff390f93", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nceph: fix memory leak in ceph_direct_read_write()\n\nThe bvecs array which is allocated in iter_get_bvecs_alloc() is leaked\nand pages remain pinned if ceph_alloc_sparse_ext_map() fails.\n\nThere is no need to delay the allocation of sparse_ext map until after\nthe bvecs array is set up, so fix this by moving sparse_ext allocation\na bit earlier.  Also, make a similar adjustment in __ceph_sync_read()\nfor consistency (a leak of the same kind in __ceph_sync_read() has been\naddressed differently).", "datePublished": "2024-12-29T08:48:44", "dateUpdated": "2025-01-20T06:26:39", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/44e518abbb498075ae85c7d1d1a503a6bb05ea2d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/eb9041837123f31d5897e99bb761f46cb4ce5859", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/66e0c4f91461d17d48071695271c824620bed4ef"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-56710"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "30f5a43c-decd-3fc3-93ad-fc6dc6c88551", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "03bc06c7b0bd8d86b9f17f459acaeb1283ba2700 <44e518abbb498075ae85c7d1d1a503a6bb05ea2d"}, {"id": "350ca583-1efe-3193-a89d-62f7db3d618a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "3817d1c2-98ae-3b95-8902-d964702c472f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.69"}, {"id": "461f2bb0-d9a7-31ca-a5f2-9d5c10ff6c60", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "52825267-fab3-3d18-b97a-746281d6daa7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "03bc06c7b0bd8d86b9f17f459acaeb1283ba2700 <66e0c4f91461d17d48071695271c824620bed4ef"}, {"id": "5aec148d-f145-3e47-a432-26812dfd94ca", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.6"}, {"id": "8d4da5d0-eddf-3a29-b432-83fdd7dfec03", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "pat